The paper deals with text generation from graph-structured data, which is a problem in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new encoder based on graph convolutional networks, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (ML) for structured data. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses two datasets that involve images and captions, which could make it relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
